body:
Hi I was playing a game on Summoner&#039;s Rift where I was hearing Static sounds which was irritating me, So I Quit the game and rejoin within a matter of 30 seconds and then my team and I finish and win the Game, everyone was normal just as per every other game, I had the option to skip stats which I did because it was taking too long to load, I then went to view my profile on League and view my Match History and then I signed out and Closed League of Legends, I reloaded League and signed back in as a friend and I made plans to play together, as I sign in I get this pop up on my Screen saying 
&quot;Game Abandoned&quot; 
&#039;You have left a game in Progress. Please reconnect to the game.&#039;

So I click reconnect and then another pop up with a blank screen this time
The pop up said 

&quot;Unable to connect to the server. Please check your network connection and attempt to reconnect to your game.&quot;
I am given two options to click either being 
&quot;Cancel&quot; or &quot;Retry&quot;

I click retry and then the same pop up comes again, Ive quit league, uninstalled it, reinstalled it, same pop ups, Ive deleted files that were suggest from reading posts on the Forums here, which reinstalled the files and then I signed in again and still says I&#039;m in a game, WHICH I AM NOT, Please Help!!!!
